race.description: Petch Nuea Stable Thailand Trophy Hcp (Bm55)
race.comment: THE WELLIAN (2) showed a great turn of foot to win a 70 by 4L this track/trip. He was then expected to repeat the dose but didn't get into it (vet cleared). Prepared to forgive that, and he's back in grade with a handy 3kg claim. Deserves another chance. EASTOWN (5) brings a comfortable win and a lip defeat this track/trip and is still on an upward trajectory. Has a wide gate today and that will require a good ride. FITZROY STREET (7) draws even wider but expect sharp improvement second up. His best is good enough and the longer journey suits. Needs luck, but the 3kg claim brings her into it. BLACK MINTO (4) is a leader who's been within range in stronger races . Will jump and run from the inside barrier and the 3kg claim brings her right into it.
